{{for|the language|Hibito language}}
The '''Jibito''' are an [[indigenous peoples of the Americas|indigenous people]] of [[Peru]]. They first met with the [[Franciscans]] monks in 1676 in the forest near the [[Huallaga River]], in what is now Peru's [[Loreto Province]]. After their conversion to [[Catholicism]], they settled in villages on the western bank of the river.<ref>{{EB1911 |wstitle=Jibitos |volume=15 |page=414 |inline=1}}</ref>

